messages.text:
Thanks, Anthony, but Jeff said this in the Haven group: ".. the testnet will run for a few months and then mainnet, you'll also be one of the first to gain access so yes, you're super early"

I know that the testnet has been running internally but I get the impression from this that Jeff is talking about the public testnet (which those of us who register get early access to), then followed by mainnet for everyone (and I doubt you'd want to skip the phase of a public testnet entirely!)

So my take from what Jeff says is that mainnet live by 1/1/2024 looks unrealistic by this reckoning

Since the emission schedule for esH1 is pre-defined you could technically assign esH1 tokens to YLD holders without a mainnet in place, but they'd obviously have to wait for a functioning block chain to use them in earnest

Feel free to correct me if my understanding is off beam
